From the moment I saw your first kick on the ultrasound, despite all the doctors saying I would lose you between 17-20 weeks and sending me home with paperwork for surrogacy, I had this feeling in my heart you would make it through for me. I’ve always felt so connected to you. And I cannot explain our bond to people when they ask. It started even before I met you. Your birth was another struggle to overcome but you made it through and I thank God every day. You’ve exceeded every expectation I’ve ever had. You came out with bright blue eyes, very fair skin, blondish light brown curly hair- it was hard to accept at first and I struggled with people asking if I was the nanny ALL THE TIME! But this is something you always do and have done- you surprise me, every damn day. To the child who has never eaten a birthday cake, the one who gets excited about dumplings and sushi but not pizza, the kid who cried happy tears jumping up and down hugging me thanking me for his electric pencil sharpener to do his homework. (WTF!!) The boy who is empathetic and sensitive but tries hard not to show it, it always ends up coming out doesn’t it? The mamma’s boy who isn’t embarrassed of me (yet) who still thinks I’m pretty cool. The kid who rather have lengthy conversation about life than play. You have such an old soul and the music you love proves it. I can’t wait to jam with you one day and create more magical moments together. 
Happy birthday, Z. Love your Mamma.

Yesterday was Martin Luther King Junior’s bday and if you’ve watched through my instastories Z is literally obsessed with him after learning about him this past week at school.  So last night at dinner he asked if for our bedtime prayer tonight we could do one “for Martin Luther King Jr.” I wanted to laugh and Michael was looking at me like (wtf) 😂 but obviously we did without question! It was so sweet watching as he thanked God for Martin Luther King Jr. I’m telling you he has been so affected by the story of segregation merely for the color of your skin.  He doesn’t see himself as “white” because he is mixed so I think he felt even more shocked and disturbed by it. (Do you remember his self portraits I posted on instastory 😬😂) He said to me “mamma you would have to be separated from babbo” 😂😭 This was just too sweet not to share. We don’t practice just one religion, this just instills security and peace in his heart. We are spiritual, believe in a God and celebrate Christmas, Chanukah and Eid.  The more the merrier. 🙏🏾 #martinlutherking

2020 I hope to live and raise my son in a world full of acceptance and love. No homophobia, no racism, just pure equality. The kid came home from school today talking about Martin Luther King and the great divide by the color of skin. He was so sad and in disbelief that actually happened. “Mamma can you actually believe they couldn’t go to the same school or even play with their friends because of their skin color?!!” I’m nervous for him to find out more about the world we lived and are living in. I wish I could shelter him from it all but the truth will come out whether I like it or not. I hope though, that he can see a massive change in us, in society and be happy and proud that we’ve come a “long way” from ignorance and stupidity. Do better, be better- for my son and if not for your future children, do it for today. #freedom #happiness #love #acceptance #nohomophobia #noracism #justlove

I hope you all had a beautiful holiday spent with family and loved ones. I’ve been living in the present, enjoying my fam and friends before Big Bear tomorrow!! Christmas Day we woke up to open gifts (mainly for Z) my favorite part of Christmas morning is watching his face as he opens them up. My dad gave his annual speech aka lecture that he sneaks in at any important engagement any chance he gets which was followed by a massive Egyptian breakfast. Both things hard to digest we went to the Grove followed by The Beverly Hills hotel for a drink by the pool. The weather was pretty terrible but nothing compares to the cold in NYC so we’re happy with anything in double digits. After that we ran home to watch the Laker game and have another Egyptian feast that was dinner. Just to add, this year we are 12 people total in the house for Christmas. I love it. After dinner and a terrible loss (Lakers) we sat to watch one of my dads favorite movies: “Meet me in St. Louis” a classic we used to always watch together as kids. We didn’t make it past 30 minutes and all passed out at 930pm. Sad the holidays are over but I’m also grateful to be living them, really truly living them without my phone or anything to take me away from the present. 🎄

SWIPE FOR THE FUNNIEST MOMENTS! 
From the back of the bathroom to my annual Christmas Eve Party. Egyptian, American, Italian, Muslim, Jewish, Catholic, gay and straight from all different backgrounds... as I looked around the party my heart felt so full. Not one person looked or thought the same and I love that about my people. No one cares about likes, followers, we are all so accepting, loving and open minded. I am honored and proud to call these people friends and family. Each year this party gets bigger with the additions of significant others, kids, friends, family. Some of my friends I have known since the 3rd grade and now we share memories with our own kids, some I’ve known for 12 years and some we are welcoming into the family as we become a small nation. 😬 ❤️🙏🏾 feeling blessed.

Swipe to last for the best pic ever!!!Missed my first flight EVER last Sunday. I have traveled to so many places, taken thousands of flights and I have never missed one!! I use to pride myself on never missing a flight and then it happened. We woke up at 5am- brushed my teeth, washed face, put on face lotion and left, got to the airport aka Zoo with lines everywhere for everything. We finally arrive to our gate after they switched it on us and they had closed it seconds before. I was pissed! @delta was on my shit list. So many people were losing their flights because they close the doors indefinitely and too early! Long story short, we waited 7 hours in the lounge which wasn’t bad and took the next direct flight with seats all the way near the bathroom 🤢 made me so nauseous but we arrived to L.A. safely with our luggage waiting for us from the original flight. Holiday travel is fun said no one ever 😂  #holidaytravel #kevin #homealone #delta  #makeupfree
